reviewText: This two-disc set was a pleasent find. There are five films in this collection: "If You Meet Sartana, Pray For Your Death", "I Am Sartana, Trade Your Guns For A Coffin:, "Blindman", "Run, Man, Run", and "Strangers Gundown". If You already own "Spaghetti Western Bible Volume 2: The Complete Sartana Saga" then yes dear reader, you would be duplicating the Sartana films. "Run, Man, Run" has been released already via Blue Underground (with a nice vintage) Spaghetti western Documentary.However, "Blindman" has not been released. Even more so, "The Strangers Gundown" was released by VCI and is now long out of print and going used for no less than $40.00 at the moment. This set is a worthy investment indeed.*side not* However, the print of "I Am Sartana, Trade Your Guns For A Coffin" is full frame only (as it is on the Sartana Saga).

reviewText: I've become addicted to Spaghetti westerns. I've been picking up the Spaghetti Western Bible series, and saw this in the suggestion tab. Since it was only 6 bucks, I thought I'd check it out. Glad I did - this set is pretty good overall if you like these kind of films, but is worth it just for 'My Name is Sartana - Trade your guns for a coffin'.In my opinion, one of the most entertaining westerns I have ever seen.Pretty good picture quality for one of these compilation sets - a couple look like they were mastered from a laserdisc or DVD rather than the usual medium quality VHS transfer you get when you buy a multi movie set. Highly recommended for fans of the genre.

reviewText: I am 75% of watching the first movie in this collection. I LOVE IT. This is a Spaghetti Western in every since of the word. It's action, killing, card playing, good guy, bad guy. You have the double cross. There is the stoic loner hero. This is my kinda western. If you have read any of my reviews on westerns, you know I NEVER saw a western I didn't enjoy.

reviewText: If you like or love Spaghetti Westerns, these 5 movies are for you. Believe it or not, Beatles Ringo Starr actually does a good job acting in Blind man, as a bandit. Klaus Kinski as always plays a creepy character in, If You Meet Sartana, Pray For Your Death. Overall they are worth the money if you like westerns.
